  "prompt": "I confessed my feelings to my crush and she became very angry. What should I do?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear that your confession didn't go as you hoped. It's important to approach the situation with sensitivity and respect for both your feelings and hers. Here are some steps you might consider:\n\n1. **Give Her Space**: It may be best to give her some time and space to process the situation. Respect her need for distance and don't pressure her for a response or explanation right away.\n\n2. **Reflect on the Situation**: Consider why she might have reacted angrily. There could be many reasons\u2014she might feel surprised, uncomfortable, or perhaps she had different expectations of your relationship.\n\n3. **Communicate Openly**: If she's willing to talk, you might want to have an open and honest conversation. Apologize if your confession made her uncomfortable and let her know you respect her feelings and boundaries.\n\n4. **Respect Her Boundaries**: Regardless of the outcome, it's crucial to respect her wishes. If she needs space or doesn\u2019t want to pursue a romantic relationship, it's important to honor that.\n\n5. **Focus on Yourself**: Take care of your own emotional well-being. Talk to friends or engage in activities that make you feel good. It can also help to journal or reflect on your feelings during this time.\n\n6. **Seek Closure**: If the opportunity arises, seek closure for yourself, but avoid forcing it from her. Understand that not all situations will have a clear resolution.\n\n7. **Move Forward**: Over time, focus on moving forward. This experience, while painful, is a part of life and can eventually lead to personal growth and understanding in future relationships.\n\nRemember that one person's reaction doesn't define your worth or ability to form meaningful connections in the future.",
